sub_title: Master Student at KIT Royal Tropical Institute, OKP Scholar | Public Health Professional | Ambassador, One Young World | BDS
summary:
Young, passionate public health practitioner with non-profit project management experience. Skilled in programmatic help, in-depth research, and intercultural communication. Competent in proposal development, data analysis, and field research.

My purpose is to pursue a career in academics while simultaneously working in an area that is undergoing rapid advancement so that I may acquire new skills and improve the ones I already possess in order to achieve both my personal and professional goals. I researched microbiology and pharmacology in addition to public health.
